abstract: Donald J Trump, in series of interviews, sketches out his plans for first 100 days of hypothetical Trump presidency in effort to reassure both voters and Republican Party of merits of his candidacy, now that he has become party's presumptive nominee; describes making Oval Office into kind of high-powered board room, among other plans.
lead_paragraph: The presumptive Republican nominee has already been giving some thought to what he would do in his first hundred days in office.

headline.main: ‘President Trump?’ Here’s How He Says It Would Look
headline.print_headline: ‘President Trump?’ Here’s How He Says It Would Look
